# CODEOWNERS — per-folder ownership for the multi-site monorepo.
# Each site is owned by its SEO Manager; the shared engine by the maintainer.
# Doc: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# A site's SEO Manager only owns their sites/<site-slug>/ subtree;
# any change to the shared engine requires the maintainer's review.
#
# ⚠️ MAINTAINER NOTE — this file blocks nothing by itself: CODEOWNERS only assigns
# reviewers. The engine is actually protected because `main` carries a branch
# protection rule with "Require a pull request before merging" + "Require review
# from Code Owners" (active since 2026-07-16, repo public). If the repo ever goes
# back to private/Free, that rule stops applying and the protection becomes a
# convention again.

# --- Default: shared engine (maintainer) ---------------------------------------
*                                   @Sam-SEO-maker

# --- Engine / core (explicit, locked) ------------------------------------------
/_shared/                           @Sam-SEO-maker
/scripts/                           @Sam-SEO-maker
/cli/                               @Sam-SEO-maker
/content_writer.py                  @Sam-SEO-maker
/.claude/                           @Sam-SEO-maker
/.github/                           @Sam-SEO-maker

# --- Site folders ---------------------------------------------------------------
# An SEO Manager only owns their own subtree. MAINTAINER STEP at each onboarding
# (the SEO Manager cannot edit .github/): add a line
# `/sites/<site-slug>/  @Sam-SEO-maker @<github-handle>` below.
# The sparse-checkout (onboarding/) isolates the disk; CODEOWNERS enforces review.
# Walkthrough: onboarding/README.md.
/sites/enseigna.fr/                 @Sam-SEO-maker
/sites/superprof.fr-ressources/     @Sam-SEO-maker
